<image 1>The sinoatrial (SA) node is indicated by ________.

A. A
B. B
C. C
D. D
E. E

To determine which label indicates the sinoatrial (SA) node, we need to identify the location of the SA node in the heart. The SA node is located in the right atrium, near the opening of the superior vena cava.

Looking at the image:
- Label A points to the superior vena cava.
- Label B points to the right atrium.
- Label C points to the right ventricle.
- Label D points to the left ventricle.
- Label E points to the left atrium.

Since the SA node is located in the right atrium, the correct answer is:

B. B
